data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530919\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104phs1665702879738.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/phs1665702879738.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/phs1665702879738.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"phs1665702879738\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Configuring the Web Test Environment\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface provides a default web environment that allows you to test your web applications. This is automatically configured during installation.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"phs1665702879738__context_w7261ab1b5b1_w7262ab1b5_w7263ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"phs1665702879738__topic_d30467e1_d30468e1_d30469e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"phs1665702879738__p_d30470e1_d30471e1_d30472e1\">You can use the following URL in the browser of your choice to run a server page component:</p>\n<kbd class=\"ph userinput\">http://<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServerName</var>:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Port</var>/uniface/wrd/<var class=\"keyword varname\">ComponentName</var>\n</kbd>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"phs1665702879738__p_d30473e1_d30474e1_d30475e1\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">http://localhost:8080/uniface/wrd/MY_DSP</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"phs1665702879738__p_d30476e1_d30477e1_d30478e1\">Check the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">urouter_machine</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tomcat_port</span> settings in the [install] section of <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> if you do not know the machine name and port number used to address the web server,</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Default Test Environment</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__1\">Item</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"exm1665702529212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exm1665702529212.html\" title=\"The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications.\">Uniface Router</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__2\">Server that handles all communication\n\t\t\t\t between Uniface client applications and the Uniface Servers that execute the client requests.\n\t\t\t\t </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"upi1665702529312.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upi1665702529312.html\" title=\"A Uniface Server is a server-based process that handles requests for remote data and component execution that it receives from client applications.\">Uniface Server</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__2\">Server that enables Uniface clients to\n                     access remote resources or to execute remote components. The Uniface Router is\n                     responsible for all communication between the client and server. For more\n                     information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"exm1665702529212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exm1665702529212.html\" title=\"The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications.\">Uniface Router</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cff1665702741216.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cff1665702741216.html\" title=\"Apache Tomcat is an open-source Java EE (Enterprise Edition)-compliant web server which is included in the Uniface installation.\">Apache Tomcat</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__2\">Web server including a servlet engine.\n\t\t\t\t </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ctl1665702541086.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ctl1665702541086.html\" title=\"The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) is used to deploy Uniface web applications. It is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering requests and maintaining connections between web servers and the Uniface Router. The WRD communicates with the Uniface Server via the Uniface Router.\">Web Request Dispatcher (WRD)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__2\">WRD is a servlet that runs in Apache\n\t\t\t\t Tomcat. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yda1665702742322.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yda1665702742322.html\" title=\"Configuration file of the web application.\">web.xml</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__2\">Configuration file for a web application.\n\t\t\t\t It contains the configuration settings for the Uniface servlets (WRD and SRD). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrd1665702718309.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrd1665702718309.html\" title=\"Assignment file for the Uniface Router. You can use the urouter.asn file to specify settings, paths to connectors, and Uniface Server environment definitions, such as USTs.\">urouter.asn</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__2\">Uniface Router assignment file. Among\n\t\t\t\t other things, it defines the path to the Uniface Server. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ahf1665702750957.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ahf1665702750957.html\" title=\"The wasv.asn file is a basic assignment file for the Web Application Server.\">wasv.asn</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"phs1665702879738__table_d3143e1_d3144e1_d3145e1__entry__2\">Assignment file for the Uniface Server.\n\t\t\t\t References in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">urouter.asn</span> file. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"phs1665702879738__li_d15398e1_d15399e1_d15400e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"phs1665702879738__p_d30479e1_d30480e1_d30481e1\">If necessary, in Uniface startup group, click\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Start Tomcat Service</span> to start the Tomcat Web server. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">By default, this is automatically started. If you modify the\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span>file, you need to stop and then start WRD for the\n                  change to take effect.</p>\n<div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"phs1665702879738__note_w7264ab1b5b3b1b3b3_w7265ab1b5b3b1b3_w7266ab1b5b3b1_w7267ab1b5b3_w7268ab1b5_w7269ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> The Uniface testing environment uses default style sheets. If you\n                  modify these, restart the WRD, and then the Uniface IDE. They will be used in both\n                  the IDE and testing environment.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"phs1665702879738__li_d15401e1_d15402e1_d15403e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"phs1665702879738__p_d30482e1_d30483e1_d30484e1\">Check that the WRD is running by entering the\n               following URL:\n                  <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">http://localhost:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Port</var>/uniface/wrd/WRD_Version</kbd></span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">This displays the Uniface Test Middleware Response page, showing the current WRD\n                  version information.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"phs1665702879738__fig_jyn_mh3_rcc\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Uniface Test Middleware Response Page</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Uniface Test Server Page\" class=\"image\" id=\"phs1665702879738__image_qys_qh3_rcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/Uniface-Test-Server-Page.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"phs1665702879738__p_d30491e1_d30492e1_d30493e1\">The servlet setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">TESTABLE</span>\n                  must be <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>, which it is by default. For more information, see\n                     <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tvq1665702743685.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tvq1665702743685.html\" title=\"Specifies whether the test page (Uniface Test Middleware Response ) can be displayed.\">TESTABLE</a>. </p>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/umx1665702765900.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Debugging in a Web Environment</a><p>Debugging in a web environment requires special techniques because there is no Uniface client application to debug. For each HTTP request, Uniface starts an instance of the requested server page, and terminates it after the request is handled.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530919\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530919\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring the Web Test Environment Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configuring the Web Test Environment Uniface provides a default web environment that allows you to test your web applications. This is automatically configured during installation. You can use the following URL in the browser of your choice to run a server page component: http:// ServerName : Port /uniface/wrd/ ComponentName For example: http://localhost:8080/uniface/wrd/MY_DSP Copy Check the urouter_machine and tomcat_port settings in the [install] section of usys.ini if you do not know the machine name and port number used to address the web server, Table 1. Default Test Environment Item Description Uniface Router Server that handles all communication between Uniface client applications and the Uniface Servers that execute the client requests. Uniface Server Server that enables Uniface clients to access remote resources or to execute remote components. The Uniface Router is responsible for all communication between the client and server. For more information, see Uniface Router . Apache Tomcat Web server including a servlet engine. Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) WRD is a servlet that runs in Apache Tomcat. web.xml Configuration file for a web application. It contains the configuration settings for the Uniface servlets (WRD and SRD). urouter.asn Uniface Router assignment file. Among other things, it defines the path to the Uniface Server. wasv.asn Assignment file for the Uniface Server. References in the urouter.asn file. If necessary, in Uniface startup group, click Start Tomcat Service to start the Tomcat Web server. By default, this is automatically started. If you modify the web.xml file, you need to stop and then start WRD for the change to take effect. Tip: The Uniface testing environment uses default style sheets. If you modify these, restart the WRD, and then the Uniface IDE. They will be used in both the IDE and testing environment. Check that the WRD is running by entering the following URL: http://localhost: Port /uniface/wrd/WRD_Version This displays the Uniface Test Middleware Response page, showing the current WRD version information. Figure 1. Uniface Test Middleware Response Page The servlet setting TESTABLE must be True , which it is by default. For more information, see TESTABLE . Related Links Debugging in a Web Environment Debugging in a web environment requires special techniques because there is no Uniface client application to debug. For each HTTP request, Uniface starts an instance of the requested server page, and terminates it after the request is handled. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}